Abhijin Adiga is a senior research associate at the Network Dynamics and Simulation Science Laboratory (NDSSL), Biocomplexity Institute of Virginia Tech. His interests are in network science, algorithms, combinatorics and game theory with current focus on design, implementation and analysis of complex simulation systems. From October 2011 to May 2014, he was a postdoctoral associate at the same department. He received his PhD degree from the Department of Computer Science & Automation, Indian Institute of Science in 2011 on dimensional parameters of graphs and posets. His paper in AAAI'13 received "Honorable Mention For Outstanding Novelty of Research Question" award.  

http://www.vbi.vt.edu/ndssl/people/people-profile/Abhijin-Adiga
